Project-specific notes

  1. This software is intended for educational and non-commercial use by
     schools, students, and developers learning about full-stack
     application design.

  2. If you fork this project for your own school, please retain visible
     attribution somewhere in the application — for example, in the About
     or Settings page.

  3. You are encouraged to share improvements back. The project welcomes
     pull requests, especially around accessibility, regional language
     support, and additional reporting formats.

  4. The default demo data (sample students, teachers, marks) is fictional
     and provided as scaffolding. Replace it with real data before
     deploying to a school.

  5. The receipts and reports produced by this software are intended as
     internal records. Verify that they meet local statutory and tax
     requirements before relying on them for compliance.

